I80ÿ1A1231

I89. Abandoned Mine Reclamation Fund

I19(a) Establishment; administration; State funds

I11There is created on the books of the Treasury of the United States a trust fund to be known as the Abandoned Mine Reclamation Fund (hereinafter referred to as the ``fund'') which shall be administered by the Secretary of the Interior. State abandoned mine reclamation funds (State funds) generated by grants from this subchapter shall be established by each State pursuant to an approved State program.

I19(b) Sources of deposits to fund

I11The fund shall consist of amounts deposited in the fund, from time to time derived from_

I12(1) the reclamation fees levied under section 1232 of this title;

I12(2) any user charge imposed on or for land reclaimed pursuant to this subchapter after expenditures for maintenance have been deducted;

I12(3) donations by persons, corporations, associations, and foundations for the purposes of this subchapter;

I12(4) recovered moneys as provided for in this subchapter; and

I12(5) interest credited to the fund under subsection (e) of this section.

I19(c) Use of moneys

I11Moneys in the fund may be used for the following purposes:

I12(1) reclamation and restoration of land and water resources adversely affected by past coal mining, including but not limited to reclamation and restoration of abandoned surface mine areas, abandoned coal processing areas, and abandoned coal refuse disposal areas; sealing and filling abandoned deep mine entries and voids; planting of land adversely affected by past coal mining to prevent erosion and sedimentation; prevention, abatement, treatment, and control of water pollution created by coal mine drainage including restoration of stream beds, and construction and operation of water treatment plants; prevention, abatement, and control of burning coal refuse disposal areas and burning coal in situ; prevention, abatement, and control of coal mine subsidence; and establishment of self-sustaining, individual State administered programs to insure private property against damages caused by land subsidence resulting from underground coal mining in those States which have reclamation plans approved in accordance with section 1253 of this title: T3ProvidedK, That funds used for this purpose shall not exceed $3,000,000 of the funds made available to any State under section 1232(g)(1) of this title;

I12(2) acquisition and filling of voids and sealing of tunnels, shafts, and entryways under section 1239 of this title;

I12(3) acquisition of land as provided for in this subchapter;

I12(4) enforcement and collection of the reclamation fee provided for in section 1232 of this title;

I12(5) restoration, reclamation, abatement, control, or prevention of adverse effects of coal mining which constitutes an emergency as provided for in this subchapter;

I12(6) grants to the States to accomplish the purposes of this subchapter;

I12(7) administrative expenses of the United States and each State to accomplish the purposes of this subchapter;

I12(8) for use under section 1240a of this title;

I12(9) for the purpose of section 1257(c) of this title, except that not more than $10,000,000 shall annually be available for such purpose;

I12(10) for the purpose described in section 1232(h) of this title; and

I12(11) all other necessary expenses to accomplish the purposes of this subchapter.

I19(d) Availability of moneys; no fiscal year limitation

I79(1) In general

I12Moneys from the fund for expenditures under subparagraphs (A) through (D) of section 1232(g)(3) of this title shall be available only when appropriated for those subparagraphs.

I79(2) No fiscal year limitation

I12Appropriations described in paragraph (1) shall be made without fiscal year limitation.

I79(3) Other purposes

I12Moneys from the fund shall be available for all other purposes of this subchapter without prior appropriation as provided in subsection (f).

I19(e) Interest

I11The Secretary of the Interior shall notify the Secretary of the Treasury as to what portion of the fund is not, in his judgment, required to meet current withdrawals. The Secretary of the Treasury shall invest such portion of the fund in public debt securities with maturities suitable for achieving the purposes of the transfers under section 1232(h) of this title and bearing interest at rates determined by the Secretary of the Treasury, taking into consideration current market yields on outstanding marketable obligations of the United States of comparable maturities. The income on such investments shall be credited to, and form a part of, the fund for the purpose of the transfers under section 1232(h) of this title.

I19(f) General limitation on obligation authority

I79(1) In general

I12From amounts deposited into the fund under subsection (b), the Secretary shall distribute during each fiscal year beginning after September 30, 2007, an amount determined under paragraph (2).

I79(2) Amounts

I18(A) For fiscal years 2008 through 2022

I13For each of fiscal years 2008 through 2022, the amount distributed by the Secretary under this subsection shall be equal to_

I14(i) the amounts deposited into the fund under paragraphs (1), (2), and (4) of subsection (b) for the preceding fiscal year that were allocated under paragraphs (1) and (5) of section 1232(g) of this title; plus

I14(ii) the amount needed for the adjustment under section 1232(g)(8) of this title for the current fiscal year.

I18(B) Fiscal years 2023 and thereafter

I13For fiscal year 2023 and each fiscal year thereafter, to the extent that funds are available, the Secretary shall distribute an amount equal to the amount distributed under subparagraph (A) during fiscal year 2022.

I79(3) Distribution

I18(A) In general

I13Except as provided in subparagraph (B), for each fiscal year, of the amount to be distributed to States and Indian tribes pursuant to paragraph (2), the Secretary shall distribute_

I14(i) the amounts allocated under paragraph (1) of section 1232(g) of this title, the amounts allocated under paragraph (5) of section 1232(g) of this title, and any amount reallocated under section 1240a(h)(3) of this title in accordance with section 1240a(h)(2) of this title, for grants to States and Indian tribes under section 1232(g)(5) of this title; and

I14(ii) the amounts allocated under section 1232(g)(8) of this title.

I18(B) Exclusion

I13Beginning on October 1, 2007, certified States shall be ineligible to receive amounts under section 1232(g)(1) of this title.

I79(4) Availability

I12Amounts in the fund available to the Secretary for obligation under this subsection shall be available until expended.

I79(5) Addition

I18(A) In general

I13Subject to subparagraph (B), the amount distributed under this subsection for each fiscal year shall be in addition to the amount appropriated from the fund during the fiscal year.

I18(B) Exceptions

I13Notwithstanding paragraph (3), the amount distributed under this subsection for the first 4 fiscal years beginning on and after October 1, 2007, shall be equal to the following percentage of the amount otherwise required to be distributed:

I14(i) 50 percent in fiscal year 2008.

I14(ii) 50 percent in fiscal year 2009.

I14(iii) 75 percent in fiscal year 2010.

I14(iv) 75 percent in fiscal year 2011.

